# Deutsche Sprache — Learning Tools

A small, growing collection of self-contained, single-file HTML tools for German language learning and speaking practice, hosted on GitHub Pages.

🔗 **Live site:** https://as1-design.github.io/deutschesprache/

### 🃏 German Verb Memory Cards
`german-memory-cards_basic verbs-opposites.html`

A print-and-play memory-matching card game built around 28 verb/opposite pairs (*öffnen ↔ schließen*, *kommen ↔ gehen*, *lieben ↔ hassen*, etc.).

- Screen preview of all three pages (verb fronts, opposite fronts, card backs)
- One-click print layout optimised for A4 (double-sided: fronts then backs)
- Designed for card stock + paper cutter for a clean physical deck

### 🗣️ B2.1 Anekdoten-Board (Speaking Board)
`german-speaking-board_b2.1_anecdote.html`

A digital prompt board for anecdote-style speaking practice.

- 12 topic categories, 5 questions each (60 prompts total)
- "Zufällige Frage" (random question) button for quick warm-ups
- Pop-up modal with a 60-second countdown ring, pause/reset, and a visual warning as time runs low

### 📖 Sprechreference B2 (Speaking Reference)
`sprechreference_b2.1_deutsch.html`

A mobile-first phrasebank for B2.1 oral exam preparation.

- Three sections: **Meinungen** (opinions), **Vorschläge** (suggestions), **Gesprächsführung** (turn-taking/interrupting)
- Tap a phrase once to mark it "used ✓", twice for "want to try ★", three times to clear
- Personal "Meine Sätze" tab collects everything you've marked, grouped by section
- Formal/informal (Sie/du) register noted throughout
- Inline grammar tags (e.g. Konjunktiv II) flag trickier constructions
